entry.title: Burgh Registers (Scotland) Act 1926 (repealed)
entry.summary: An Act to provide for the discontinuance of the Burgh Registers of Sasines in Scotland.

entry.title: Legitimacy Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law relating to children born out of wedlock.

entry.title: Judicial Proceedings (Regulation of Reports) Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to regulate the publication of reports of judicial proceedings in such manner as to prevent injury to public morals.

entry.title: Rating (Scotland) Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law with respect to rating in Scotland, and for purposes incidental thereto or connected therewith.

entry.title: Parks Regulation (Amendment) Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Parks Regulation Act 1872.

entry.title: Births and Deaths Registration Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law relating to certification of deaths and the disposal of the dead.

entry.title: Small Holdings and Allotments Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Small Holdings and Allotments Acts, 1908 to 1919.

entry.title: Fertilisers and Feeding Stuffs Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law with respect to the sale of fertilisers and feeding stuffs.

entry.title: Mining Industry Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to make provision for facilitating the working of minerals and the better organisation of the coal mining industry, and with respect to the welfare of persons employed therein, and for other purposes connected with that industry.

entry.title: Chartered Associations (Protection of Names and Uniforms) Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to protect the names, uniforms, and badges of associations incorporated by Royal Charter.

entry.title: Secretaries of State Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to transfer the powers of the Secretary for Scotland to one of His Majestys Principal Secretaries of State, and to increase the number of Secretaries of State and Under Secretaries of State capable of sitting and voting in the Commons House of Parliament, and for purposes connected with the matters aforesaid.

entry.title: Markets and Fairs (Weighing of Cattle) Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Markets and Fairs (Weighing of Cattle) Acts 1887 and 1891.

entry.title: First Fruits and Tenths Measure 1926 (repealed 5.11.1993)
entry.summary: A Measure passed by the National Assembly of the Church of England To provide for the extinguishment or redemption of first fruits and tenths.

entry.title: Ecclesiastical Commissioners Measure 1926
entry.summary: A Measure passed by the National Assembly of the Church of England To amend the Ecclesiastical Commissioners Acts 1840 and 1841, and the Ecclesiastical Commissioners Act 1840, Amendment Act, 1885, and to make further provision for the augmentation of archdeaconries, for aiding the endowment funds of new bishoprics, for bishops costs of legal proceedings, for the maintenance of Lambeth Palace, and the repair of other Episcopal Residences.

entry.title: Criminal Appeal (Scotland) Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law of Scotland relating to appeal in criminal cases tried on indictment.

entry.title: Execution of Diligence (Scotland) Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law relating to the execution of diligence in Scotland.

entry.title: Imperial War Graves Endowment Fund Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to provide for the incorporation of the Trustees of the Imperial War Graves Endowment Fund and for other matters connected with the said Fund.

entry.title: Law of Property (Amendment) Act 1926
entry.summary: An Act to amend certain enactments relating to the law of property and trustees.

entry.title: Administrative Provisions Act (Northern Ireland) 1926
entry.summary: An Act to make provision with respect to the administration of the public services transferred to the Government of Northern Ireland by virtue of the Ireland (Confirmation of Agreement) Act, 1925, and for purposes connected therewith.
